snippet: Kenenisa Bekele of Ethiopia, a three-time Olympic champion at 5,000 and 10,000 meters, won the Paris Marathon in his marathon debut.
abstract: Kenenisa Bekele of Ethiopia, three-time Olympic champion at 5,000 and 10,000 meters, wins Paris Marathon in his marathon debut in record 2 hours 5 minutes 4 seconds.
lead_paragraph: Kenenisa Bekele of Ethiopia, a three-time Olympic champion at 5,000 and 10,000 meters, won the Paris Marathon in his marathon debut.

headline.main: Ethiopian Wins His Debut Marathon in Paris
